text: The chicken rice and prata stalls served very good food. My go-to place when I am in the vicinity of Ubi. Be prepared to queue.

Good variety of stalls serving Chinese to Indian food. Some famous stalls include Far East chicken rice, the roast chicken is more popular. Mr Lorbak and crispy roti prata.

This coffee shop is amazing! It has a variety of delicious stalls serving food such as crispy prata, chicken rice, Teochew fish ball noodles, kway chap, and more. But the absolute standout for me is the Hokkien fried prawn noodles - they are absolutely mouthwatering! ðŸ¤¤

We came here for the crispy roti prata n are not disappointed.  Waited half an hour,  aunty will give u a beeper n call u when ready. In the meantime we ate kuay chup while waiting. Really worth the wait. Roti prata is freshly made on the spot. Really crispy and piping hot.
